# Wordly Dictionary SPA

Wordly is a Single Page Application (SPA) that lets you search for any English
word and see its pronunciation, meanings, definitions, examples, and synonyms
- all without the page ever reloading. It's built with plain HTML, CSS, and
JavaScript, and gets its word data from a free public dictionary API.

## Features

- Word search
- Definitions and parts of speech
- Pronunciation text
- Audio pronunciation (when available)
- Example sentences (when available)
- Synonyms (when available)
- Favorites, saved using `localStorage` so they persist after closing the page
- Error handling for empty input, misspelled/unknown words, and network failures
- Responsive design (works on desktop and mobile)
- Light/dark theme toggle

## Technologies used

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript
- [Free Dictionary API](https://dictionaryapi.dev/)
- `localStorage`

## Project structure

```
wordly/
├── index.html
├── css/
│   └── style.css
├── js/
│   └── index.js
└── README.md
```

## How to run the project

1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Open the project folder.
3. Open `index.html` in your browser (or use the "Live Server" extension in
   VS Code).
4. Enter a word in the search field.

## API information

Word data comes from the **Free Dictionary API**, which requires no API key.

Endpoint format:
```
https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/api/v2/entries/en/{word}
```

The app sends the word you searched for to this endpoint and displays the
meanings, pronunciation, audio (when available), examples, synonyms, and
source links returned in the response.

## Usage

1. Enter a word.
2. Click **Search**.
3. View the definition and pronunciation details.
4. Play the audio pronunciation, if available.
5. Save or remove the word from your favorites.

